<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Remember last year when Elon Musk was going ar=
ound <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30552542.2698=
05/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDUtMTcv=
ZWxvbi1tdXNrLWRvZXMtbm90LWNhcmUtYWJvdXQtc3BhbS1ib3RzP2NtcGlkPUJCRDAyMTQyM19=
NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZX=
JtPTIzMDIxNCZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBec13b=
749" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;">  pretending</a> that Twitter Inc. was <a href=3D"https://link=
.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30552542.269805/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZ=
XJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDgtMjkvbXVzay10cmllcy1hLW5ldy13YXkt=
b3V0LW9mLXR3aXR0ZXI_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDIxNDIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWF=
pbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwMjE0JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb2=
5leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBee1f4aea" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemsc=
ope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoratio=
n: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000;=
 border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">  doing a whole assor=
tment of fraud</a>, hoping that some of it would stick so that he could get=
 out of his deal to buy Twitter? That was annoying. It did not go well, for=
 him, and he eventually dropped it and bought Twitter at the price he had o=
riginally agreed to. But if you go around telling everyone that a US public=
 company is committing all sorts of fraud, then some securities lawyers are=
 definitely going to sue the company for that alleged fraud, and they defin=
itely did.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And now Musk owns the company and has to defen=
d that fraud suit =E2=80=94=C2=A0hard, given that he has previously claimed=
 to agree with it! =E2=80=94=C2=A0or else pay damages =E2=80=94=C2=A0unfair=
, since, in the somewhat imaginary world in which Twitter was doing a bunch=
 of fraud, Musk is the biggest=C2=A0<em>victim=C2=A0</em>of that fraud! On =
the fraud theory of Twitter, Twitter was doing a bunch of fraud that proppe=
d up its stock price, and then Musk agreed to buy it at a premium to that i=
nflated price, and then the fraud was disclosed, and then Musk grumbled but=
 bought it anyway at that inflated premium price, and now the shareholders =
who=C2=A0<em>sold=C2=A0</em>get to sue=C2=A0<em>him=C2=A0</em>for more mone=
y? Seems very unfair, and yet somehow hilariously deserved.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway yesterday the plaintiffs in the federal=
 securities fraud case against Twitter filed their <a href=3D"https://link.=
mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30552542.269805/aHR0cHM6Ly9hc3NldHMuYndieC=
5pby9kb2N1bWVudHMvdXNlcnMvaXFqV0hCRmRmeElVL3JPMTlfa3RuQzJGRS92MA/607f07ceef=
4b8524a319a23cBe234bc6c" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" tar=
get=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; b=
order-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style:=
 solid; background-color: #ccc;"> amended complaint</a>. It plays all the h=
its that you might remember from last year =E2=80=94=C2=A0mDAUs! <a href=3D=
"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30552542.269805/aHR0cHM6Ly93=
d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDgtMjMvdHdpdHRlci13aGl=
zdGxlYmxvd2VyLWRvZXNuLXQtaGVscC1lbG9uLW11c2stcy1jYXNlLW11Y2g_Y21waWQ9QkJEMD=
IxNDIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImd=
XRtX3Rlcm09MjMwMjE0JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23=
cB8b2a983d" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank=
" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-=
width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backg=
round-color: #ccc;">  Mudge</a>! =E2=80=94=C2=A0and I am absolutely not goi=
ng to read or write about any of the fraud claims. The weird part is figuri=
ng out how the shareholders were, allegedly, <em>harmed</em>. Let=E2=80=99s=
 say that Twitter was doing assorted frauds that inflated its price: Musk s=
till bought it at that inflated price. So how did shareholders get hurt? Fr=
om the complaint:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In April 2022, Twitter=E2=80=99s Board accepte=
d a buyout offer from Elon Musk (=E2=80=9CMusk=E2=80=9D). Yet the deal quic=
kly soured.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On May 13, 2022, before the market opened, Mus=
k tweeted out concerns about Twitter=E2=80=99s representations concerning t=
he number of bots. Twitter=E2=80=99s stock price fell 9.7% that day, fallin=
g another 8.2% over the next day as Musk continued to tweet his concerns.</=
p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On July 7, 2022, the Washington Post reported =
that Musk had stopped engaging in certain discussions around the deal. Twit=
ter=E2=80=99s stock price fell 5.1%.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Then on July 8, 2022, Twitter publicly filed w=
ith the SEC a letter from Musk terminating the deal, citing misrepresentati=
ons concerning the number of bots. Twitter=E2=80=99s stock price plunged 11=
.3%.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On the weekend of May 14 and 15, 2022, Musk co=
ntinued to tweet about the prevalence of fake or spam accounts on Twitter. =
On May 14, Musk tweeted that his =E2=80=9Cteam will do a random sample of 1=
00 followers of @twitter=E2=80=9D to determine how many were fake or spam a=
ccounts, and that =E2=80=9CI picked 100 as the sample size because that is =
what Twitter uses to calculate &lt;5% fake/spam/duplicate.=E2=80=9D Later t=
hat same day, Musk tweeted: =E2=80=9CTwitter legal just called to complain =
that I violated their NDA by revealing the bot check sample size is 100! Th=
is actually happened.=E2=80=9D On May 15 he said in two tweets that =E2=80=
=9CI have yet to see *any* analysis that has fake/spam/duplicates at 5%=E2=
=80=9D. Further, during the trading day on May 16, 2022, in response to twe=
ets by Defendant Agrawal concerning the prevalence of fake or spam accounts=
, Musk asked on Twitter =E2=80=9CSo how do=C2=A0advertisers know what they=
=E2=80=99re getting for their money? This is fundamental to the financial h=
ealth of Twitter.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In response to this news, the price of Twitter=
=E2=80=99s common stock fell 8.18%, or $3.33, from a closing price of $40.7=
2 on May 13, 2022, to close at $37.39 on the next trading day, May 16, 2022=
.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So what? Eventually Musk bought Twitter for $5=
4.20 per share, as agreed. But I think what those passages mean=C2=A0is tha=
t if you bought Twitter stock after Musk agreed to buy Twitter, and then yo=
u <em>sold</em> it after Musk tweeted it was a fraud and the stock dropped,=
 you lost money and are entitled to compensation from Twitter. They=E2=80=
=99re suing Musk for tweeting that Twitter was a fraud. Serves him right, r=
eally.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In other news, here is a story about Musk alle=
gedly <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30552542.269=
805/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cucGxhdGZvcm1lci5uZXdzL3AvZWxvbi1tdXNrLWZpcmVzLWEtdG9wLXR=
3aXR0ZXItZW5naW5lZXI/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB51ad4dd4" itemprop=3D"StoryLi=
nk" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text=
-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color=
: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> firing an =
engineer</a> who told him that people don=E2=80=99t read his tweets because=
 they=E2=80=99ve lost interest, and here is <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bl=
oombergbusiness.com/click/30552542.269805/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cudGhldmVyZ2UuY29tL=
zIwMjMvMi8xMy8yMzU5ODUxNC90d2l0dGVyLWFsZ29yaXRobS1lbG9uLW11c2stdHdlZXRz/607=
f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB826c97dd" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemsco=
pe" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !impor=
tant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom=
-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> another story</a> about how Twitte=
r is allegedly injecting Musk=E2=80=99s tweets into users=E2=80=99 timeline=
s. Look, I mean, as a Twitter user, I do not love that Twitter is now the E=
lon Musk Show all the time. But, as a Twitter user,=C2=A0<em>he=C2=A0</em>c=
learly loves that, and he does own the company! He can do what he wants! Wh=
en he first bought shares in Twitter, <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomber=
gbusiness.com/click/30552542.269805/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGl=
uaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDQtMDQvZWxvbi1tdXNrLWJvdWdodC1zb21lLXR3aXR0ZXI_Y2=
1waWQ9QkJEMDIxNDIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld=
3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwMjE0JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4=
b8524a319a23cB8f223f4b" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" targ=
et=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bo=
rder-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: =
solid; background-color: #ccc;">  I imagined a dialogue</a> between Musk (a=
s a big but outside shareholder and a devoted user of Twitter) and then-Chi=
ef Executive Officer Parag Agrawal:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Elon Musk:</strong> Make the font bigg=
er when I tweet.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Agrawal:</strong> What?=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Musk:</strong> I am your biggest share=
holder, I want the font on my tweets to be bigger than the font on everyone=
 else=E2=80=99s tweets.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Agrawal:</strong> That=E2=80=99s not r=
eally how we=E2=80=94</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Musk:</strong> And I want 290 characte=
rs. Again, just for me.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Agrawal:</strong> =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><strong>Musk:</strong> And it should play a li=
ttle sound when I tweet so everyone knows.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Then he bought the company and fired Agrawal a=
nd everyone else who objected to this plan, so here we are I guess.</p>
