<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">You might take Point 6 to mean that meme-stock=
=C2=A0companies are=C2=A0<em>less=C2=A0</em>responsive to their owners than=
 regular companies are: Regular companies are owned by big institutions who=
 own big blocks of shares and can call the CEOs up to yell at them; meme-st=
ock companies are owned by retail investors on Robinhood who own fractional=
 shares and just complain on Reddit, where they can be ignored. Or you migh=
t take Point 7 to mean that meme-stock companies are=C2=A0<em>more=C2=A0</e=
m>responsive to their owners than regular companies are: Meme companies are=
 owned by enthusiastic shareholders with concentrated portfolios who really=
 really care, and the companies lean into their retail ownership and, like,=
 <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30552542.269805/a=
